===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|plese}} < {{etyl|fro}} {{term|plaisir}} < {{etyl|la}} {{term|placere|placēre|to please, to seem good}}.<ref name="dictionary">{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref>

====Verb====
{{en-verb|pleas|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To make [[happy]] or [[satisfy]]; to give [[pleasure]].
#: ''Her presentation '''pleased''' the executives.''
# {{intransitive|ergative}} To [[desire]]; to [[will]]; to be pleased.
#: ''Just do as you '''please'''.''

